cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.CY

This paper discusses the evaluation of blockchain protocols based on their design and properties, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also touches upon distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS) as they are relevant to blockchain technology. The paper also discusses software engineering (cs.SE) aspects of blockchain protocol design and implementation. Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of blockchain technology on society and the need for policy and decision makers to understand it, which falls under the category of computers and society (cs.CY).
